  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "1cd4750c-f3ba-80ea-9b14-e7b606a0ae11",
      "heading": "Summary Table KT",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Flaw of Previous Models",
          "Novelty of Model",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Question Correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (2)",
          "3841 learners on Assistments\n5000 students in EdNet\n6043 on KDD\n2086 on WUD",
          "Each dataset refers to its own context",
          "Questions, \nLMS logs",
          "[Memory Matrix]",
          "The current Knowledge Tracing Models based on IRT are too simple to integrate prediction of answers and connect them to the theoretical constructs of knowledge modelling.\n",
          "The new model XKT includes 3 components that together look to make this integration:\n\nMulti-Feature Embedding: a component meant to model questions.\n\nCognition Processing Network: Thew knowledge tracing model that encodes the different knowledge components.\n\nMIRT Neural Predictor: The layer that outputs predictions and parameters.\n\n\nA big distinction between this model and the previous is that Each knowledge concept is represented by a vector.",
          "Prediction of Next Question CFA is done by subdividing the task into 2 components:\n\n1. A Cueing Retrieval Network which estimates the learners’ ability based on the its current memory matrix.\n\n2. A Question difficulty model that estimates how simple/hard the question will be for the learner.",
          "DKT, Deep-IRT, DKVMN, CKT, AKT, simpleKT, LPKT-S, XKT",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "ASSIST2009:\n\n{AUC: 0.8301 - XKT}\n\nKDD:\n\n{AUC: 0.7985 - XKT}\n\nEdNet:\n\n{AUC: 0.7801 - XKT}\n\nWUC:\n\n{AUC: 0.8357 - XKT}",
          "Authors propose a new model called XKT which is not only expected to outperform current KT models but also provide explainable parameters.\n\nThe authors show that model outperforms baselines. Moreover, the authors also explore how this model addresses the cold-strat problem for both learners and questions:\n\nFor learners, XKT starts outperforming BKT for sequences of exercises that are greater than 35 questions.\n\nXKT also outperforms the remaining models when simulating coldd-start for questions.\n\nFrom an interpretation perspective, the transitions between knowledge states in XKT are smooth.\n\n",
          "Only AUC results are shown."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
